Heading -->\n      <div class=\"w-full sm:w-1\/3\">\n                  <div class=\"subtitle mb-layout-xs\">\n            <svg class=\"icon\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\">\n              <use href=\"#dot\"><\/use>\n            <\/svg>\n            FAQ          <\/div>\n                          <h2>SEO Checker FAQ&#039;s<\/h2>\n                      <\/div>\n\n      <!-- FAQ -->\n              <!-- Mark this block as an FAQPage -->\n        <div class=\"w-full sm:w-3\/5\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/FAQPage\">\n          <dl class=\"accordion lg:mt-12\" data-chris data-fade-in-childs>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">How accurate is the SEO Checker?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>The SEO Checker provides a detailed and reliable analysis of your website\u2019s SEO performance, based on proven industry metrics and benchmarks. While it\u2019s accurate for identifying common issues such as missing meta tags, broken links, or slow load times, it\u2019s important to note that no automated tool can account for every nuance of your website\u2019s unique structure or goals. For a more comprehensive assessment, <a href=\"\/contact\/\">contact us<\/a> to explore how our SEO experts can assist.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">I need help with the results from my SEO Checker.<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>If you\u2019re unsure how to interpret or act on your SEO Checker results, we\u2019re here to help. Our team of SEO experts can explain what each section means and provide tailored recommendations to improve your website\u2019s performance. Whether it\u2019s optimising your on-page content, building backlinks, or improving technical elements like site speed, <a href=\"\/contact\/\">get in touch<\/a> with us or <a href=\"\/contact\/\">send us your project brief <\/a>so we can guide you every step of the way.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">What\u2019s the difference between an SEO Checker and a manual SEO audit?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>An SEO Checker is an automated tool that provides a quick overview of your website\u2019s SEO health, highlighting key areas like keyword usage, backlinks, and technical performance. A manual SEO audit, however, is carried out by an expert who takes a more detailed look, analysing factors such as user behaviour, content strategy, competitor activity, and other more complex elements. If you\u2019re interested in a comprehensive manual audit, <a href=\"\/contact\/\">get in touch with us<\/a>.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Can the SEO Checker detect all SEO issues?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>The SEO Checker is very effective at identifying common SEO issues such as missing meta descriptions, slow page speeds, or weak backlink profiles. That said, it may not catch everything\u2014for example, it might not fully assess deeper content strategy, advanced user experience challenges, or industry-specific SEO needs. For a more in-depth evaluation, contact our SEO team to discuss a custom audit.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Will the SEO Checker show me how to fix the issues it finds?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>It will! The SEO Checker highlights the areas to improve and gives practical suggestions, like tweaking title tags, adding alt text to images, or fixing broken links. If you\u2019d prefer some extra support implementing those fixes, our team is here to lend a hand. Reach out to us, and we\u2019ll sort it out together.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Does the SEO Checker work for all website platforms (e.g., WordPress, Shopify)?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Yes, the SEO Checker works across all major website platforms, including WordPress, Shopify, Wix, and more. It evaluates universal SEO principles that apply regardless of your platform, such as meta tags, page speed, mobile responsiveness, and structured data. If you\u2019re unsure about platform-specific SEO issues, <a href=\"\/contact\/\">contact us<\/a> for support.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Should I rely on an SEO Checker or hire an SEO expert?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>An SEO Checker is a handy starting point, especially if you\u2019re new to SEO. It\u2019s great for spotting the basics, but for ongoing improvements or tackling more technical challenges, an expert can bring the experience and strategy needed to make a real impact. The two can work well together\u2014if that sounds like what you need, get in touch with us.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                      <\/dl>\n        <\/div>\n          <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/section>